# Project Structure Guide

The repository follows a monorepo layout. Key directories:

- `backend/` (FastAPI backend): main entrypoint is `backend/main.py`. Backend Dockerfile and `requirements.txt` live here.
- `frontend/` (Next.js app): app router under `frontend/app/`, `package.json`, and Dockerfile here.
- `infra/` (infrastructure): `docker-compose.yml` and database init SQL under `infra/db/init/`.
- `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`, `docs.md`, and `tasks.md` contain design docs and task templates.

When navigating the repo, prefer opening `backend/`, `frontend/`, and `infra/` folders first to find service-specific code.

Sprint focus: Sprint 3 (Agents). Useful backend endpoints for dev:
- `GET /api/resources/{id}/chunks` — inspect chunk metadata
- `POST /api/llm/preview` — iterate prompts for tagging
- `GET /api/llm/smoke` — LLM connectivity
- `POST /api/embeddings/upsert` — ensure vectors exist